name: Use centralized API client instead of direct fetch
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: Direct fetch() calls or local API state management in components
then: Use centralized apiClient from services/api.ts with proper error handling and categorization
why: Centralized client provides consistent error handling, type safety, error categorization, and reduces code duplication.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement proper API error handling
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: API calls without try-catch blocks or generic error handling
then: Use ApiError class and provide specific error messages with proper HTTP status codes
why: Proper error handling improves debugging and provides better user feedback.
globs: ["frontend/src/services/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/hooks/**/*.ts"]

---
name: Use TypeScript interfaces for API responses
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: API responses typed as 'any' or missing type annotations
then: Import and use proper interfaces from types/api.ts for all API responses
why: Type safety prevents runtime errors and provides better IDE support.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use custom hooks for API calls
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: Direct apiClient calls in components or manual loading/error state management
then: Use domain-specific hooks like useFunds(), useEntities(), useCreateFund() with centralized error handling
why: Custom hooks encapsulate API logic and provide consistent loading/error states with proper error categorization.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement proper loading states for API calls
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Components without loading indicators during API calls
then: Use loading state from custom hooks and display CircularProgress
why: Loading states provide user feedback and improve perceived performance.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use proper HTTP methods for API calls
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: Using GET for mutations or POST for data retrieval
then: Use appropriate HTTP methods: GET for retrieval, POST for creation, PUT/PATCH for updates
why: RESTful API design improves consistency and enables proper caching.
globs: ["frontend/src/services/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/hooks/**/*.ts"]

---
name: Implement proper CORS handling
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: Flask app without CORS configuration for frontend requests
then: Add CORS(app) to allow cross-origin requests from React frontend
why: CORS is required for frontend to communicate with backend API.
globs: ["src/api.py"]

---
name: Use consistent API response format
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: Inconsistent response structures across API endpoints
then: Use consistent format: {"data": [...], "error": "message", "total": count}
why: Consistent response format simplifies frontend integration and error handling.
globs: ["src/api.py", "src/api/**/*.py"]

---
name: Add proper HTTP status codes
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: API endpoints returning 200 for all responses including errors
then: Use appropriate status codes: 200 for success, 201 for creation, 400 for bad request, 404 for not found
why: Proper HTTP status codes enable proper error handling and caching.
globs: ["src/api.py", "src/api/**/*.py"]

---
name: Implement API endpoint validation
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: API endpoints without input validation
then: Validate request data at API layer before delegating to domain methods
why: Early validation prevents invalid data from reaching domain layer.
globs: ["src/api.py", "src/api/**/*.py"]

---
name: Use session management in API endpoints
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: API endpoints without proper session setup/teardown
then: Use try-finally pattern to ensure session cleanup
why: Prevents database connection leaks and ensures proper resource management.
globs: ["src/api.py", "src/api/**/*.py"]

---
name: Add API health check endpoint
scope: python
language: python
severity: info
if: Missing health check endpoint for monitoring
then: Add GET /api/health endpoint that returns 200 OK
why: Health checks enable monitoring and deployment verification.
globs: ["src/api.py"]
